  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To determine if there is a difference in the quality of life in between patients who
      undergoes laparoscopic transabdominal pre-peritoneal (TAPP) or modified Lichtenstein
      hernioplasty
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients presenting with incarcerated inguinal hernias will be randomized between open or
      laparoscopic repair groups. The primary outcome will be the quality of life scores. Patients
      will be followed-up for 12 months.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
